data.message: All of asp.net since MVC is already open source, the only parts that are not open source is WebForms
WebForms is not open source for the good of the world. Nobody wants to look at that LOL

WebForms in my opinion  was a necessary evil to bring a significant portion of windows developers to the web in a familiar way, and for the most part that happened, but it didn't innovate fast enough afterwards and to that day all the asp. Net development is just a DotNet flavor of whatever is already out there. 
To be honest the only asp.net true innovation was WebForms
Also I think that a part of the MVC core is from Webforms DLLs, Right ?
They share a lot for sure, but MVC is not built on top of WebForms.
